### Unified AI Gateway - Cache Configuration Tests
### 
### This test collection validates the metadata-config caching behavior including cache hits, 
### cache stores, cache skip, and cache refresh operations.
### Tests cross-request caching, cache skip headers, cache refresh headers, and cache status monitoring.
###
### Cache Behavior:
### - Default: Uses APIM built-in cache with configurable duration (default: 300 seconds)
### - Cache key: "metadata-config-v{version}" (version-based for automatic invalidation)
### - Version: Configured in cache-settings.config-version (change to invalidate cache)
### - TTL: Configured in cache-settings.ttl-seconds (cache duration in seconds)
### - Bypass Header: UAIG-Config-Cache-Bypass: true (bypasses cache for single request)
### - Trace sources: Central-Cache-Manager-Bypass, Central-Cache-Manager-Loaded, Central-Cache-Manager-Store
### - UAIG-Cache-Operation header values:
###     - bypass: Cache was skipped entirely (UAIG-Config-Cache-Bypass header was set to true)
###     - loaded: Configuration was retrieved from cache (cache hit)
###     - store: Configuration was parsed from fragment and stored to cache (cache miss or refresh)
### 
### Prerequisites (see ReadMe for details):
### 1. Run `azd up` to provision the infrastructure and create the VS Code settings file with all required variables
### 2. Ensure your APIM instance and backends are successfully deployed
###
### Usage:
### - Click "Send Request" above each request in VS Code with REST Client extension
### - Expected debug headers are documented for each test to validate cache behavior
### - Use UAIG-Config-Cache-Bypass header to bypass cache entirely (no read or write)
### - To refresh cache: change cache-settings.config-version in Metadata-Config.xml and run `azd up` to redeploy

# Variables from VS Code REST Client settings
@apimEndpoint = {{apim_gateway_url}}/unified-ai
@apiVersion = 2025-01-01-preview

# APIM subscription key from VS Code settings
@apimSubKey = {{apim_subscription_key}}

# Model deployment for testing
@deploymentName = gpt-4.1-mini

###############################################################################
### Test 1: Normal Request - Cache Store and Cache Load
###############################################################################

### 1a. First request - should STORE to cache (if cache is empty or expired)
# 
# Note: To guarantee fresh cache for testing:
# 1. Change cache-settings.config-version in Metadata-Config.xml and run `azd up` to redeploy, OR
# 2. Wait for cache TTL to expire (default: 300 seconds)
# 
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Cache-Operation: store
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-pool
# UAIG-Model-ID: gpt-4.1-mini
#
# Trace (App Insights): Central-Cache-Manager-Store, message: "Configuration loaded for {path}"
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/{{deploymentName}}/chat/completions?api-version={{apiVersion}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Say 'Cache Test 1' please"
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 10
}

### 1b. Second identical request - should be CACHE HIT (if within 300 second window)
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Cache-Operation: loaded
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-pool
# UAIG-Model-ID: gpt-4.1-mini
#
# Trace (App Insights): Central-Cache-Manager-Loaded, message: "Configuration loaded from cache for {path}"
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/{{deploymentName}}/chat/completions?api-version={{apiVersion}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Say 'Cache Test 1b' please"
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 10
}

###############################################################################
### Test 2: Cache Skip Using UAIG-Config-Cache-Bypass Header
###############################################################################

### 2a. Request with cache bypass header - bypasses cache entirely
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Cache-Operation: bypass
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-pool
# UAIG-Model-ID: gpt-4.1-mini
#
# Trace (App Insights): Central-Cache-Manager-Bypass, message: "Cache bypass requested for {path}"
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/{{deploymentName}}/chat/completions?api-version={{apiVersion}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
UAIG-Config-Cache-Bypass: true
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Say 'cache skip Test' please"
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 10
}

### 2b. Request with cache bypass header set to 'false' (should use cache normally)
# Expected Debug Headers:
# UAIG-Cache-Operation: loaded (should use cached config from Test 1)
# UAIG-Selected-Backend: standard-pool
# UAIG-Model-ID: gpt-4.1-mini
POST {{apimEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/{{deploymentName}}/chat/completions?api-version={{apiVersion}}
api-key: {{apimSubKey}}
UAIG-Config-Cache-Bypass: false
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "messages": [
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Say 'No Skip' please"
        }
    ],
    "max_tokens": 10
}

